Lawrence Scott Hershfield: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 11:52 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Ranch Capital, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Lawrence Scott Hershfield  Chief Executive Officer, Ranch Capital, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Lawrence Scott Hershfield, also known as Larry, is the Founder at Ranch Capital, LLC and has been its Chief Executive Officer since October 2002. He is responsible for the strategic direction of the firm, sourcing and analyzing prospective investments, and managing the firm on a day-to-day basis. Since June 2004, Mr. Hershfield has been the Chief Executive Officer and the President of RC Aviation Management, LLC, the managing member of RC Aviation. From 1996 to 1998, ... he served as the Chief Executive Officer and the President of Pepsi International Bottlers. Mr. Hershfield worked for 17 years with Leucadia National Corporation in positions of increasing responsibility, culminating as its Executive Vice President of Leucadia International. From 1995 to September 2002, he served as the President of Leucadia International Corporation. Mr. Hershfield served as the Chief Executive Officer and the President of Hawaiian Holdings Inc, from June 14, 2004 to June 2, 2005. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of The FINOVA Group, Inc., since August 2001 until September 2002. In addition to his extensive investment experience in distressed or bankrupt companies, Mr. Hershfield ran three companies during his Leucadia career, including BRAE Corporation, Pepsi International Bottlers and Finova. He also has significant international experience, including three-and-a-half years in Russia and serving as a Director of a Latin American utility company. Mr. Hershfield serves as a Director of Compania Boliviana de Energia Electrica S.A. - Bolivian Power Company Limited. He worked for five years in various capacities at BRAE Corporation, ultimately being named President in 1986 after Leucadia purchased a controlling interest in the firm. Mr. Hershfield has been the Chairman of Hawaiian Holdings Inc, since July 2004 and also served as the Chairman of the Board of Hawaiian Airlines for 11 years. He is a Board Member of Berkadia, LLC and previously served as the Chairman of the Board of Premier Entertainment Biloxi. Mr. Hershfield is also the Chairman of the Board of 5D Robotics, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Hawaiian Holdings Inc, since July 2004. Mr. Hershfield serves as a Director of Bolivian Power Company. He has been a Director of Infinity Bio-Energy Ltd. since December 2007. Mr. Hershfield served as Member of Advisory Board at 3Dsize.com, Inc. He served as a Director of The FINOVA Group, Inc., from August 2001 to September 2002 and Pepsi International Bottlers from 1996 to 1998. Mr. Hershfield serves on the Advisory Board of the Stanford Center for Longevity and previously as a Trustee of the Stanford University Graduate School of Business Trust and of La Jolla Country Day School. He received a B.S. in Biology from Bucknell University, summa cum laude, in 1977 and an M.B.A. from Stanford University Graduate School of Business in 1981.Read Full Background




